451
00:29:51.426 --> 00:29:53.595
A dangerous pastime.

452
00:29:53.678 --> 00:29:54.971
-I know.

453
00:29:55.054 --> 00:29:58.099
<i>But that wacky old coot is Belle's father</i>

454
00:29:58.683 --> 00:30:01.269
<i>And his sanity's only so-so</i>

455
00:30:01.770 --> 00:30:04.856
<i>Now the wheels in my head</i>
<i>Have been turning</i>


456
00:30:05.106 --> 00:30:08.109
<i>
-Since I looked at that loony old man</i>

457
00:30:08.276 --> 00:30:11.654
<i>See, I promised myself</i>
<i>I'd be married to Belle</i>


458
00:30:11.821 --> 00:30:15.825
<i>And right now</i>
<i>I'm evolving a plan</i>


459
00:30:17.535 --> 00:30:18.536
-If I...
-Yes?


460
00:30:18.661 --> 00:30:19.662
-Then we...
-No, will she?


461
00:30:19.788 --> 00:30:21.539
-Yes.
-Now I get it.


462
00:30:21.998 --> 00:30:24.501
Let's go!

463
00:30:25.502 --> 00:30:29.464
<i>No one plots like Gaston</i>

464
00:30:29.547 --> 00:30:31.174
<i>Takes cheap shots like Gaston</i>

465
00:30:31.257 --> 00:30:34.636
<i>Plans to persecute harmless</i>
<i>Crackpots like Gaston</i>


466
00:30:34.719 --> 00:30:40.475
<i>So his marriage</i>
<i>We soon will be celebrating</i>


467
00:30:40.558 --> 00:30:47.440
<i>My, what a guy, Gaston</i>

468
00:30:54.531 --> 00:30:55.657
Hmm?

469
00:31:10.129 --> 00:31:13.633
There has to be some way
we can cheer up Belle.


470
00:31:14.342 --> 00:31:17.554
-Help her see the bright side.
-I've got it!


471
00:31:19.222 --> 00:31:21.349
Why don't you show her
your little TikTok dance?


472
00:31:21.432 --> 00:31:22.851
That always cheers me up.

473
00:31:23.017 --> 00:31:24.894
It's not a dance.
It's the way I walk.


474
00:31:25.061 --> 00:31:26.896
And tick-tock is the sound
I make when I move.


475
00:31:27.063 --> 00:31:28.064
Ah.

476
00:31:32.151 --> 00:31:34.612
Oh, I'm suddenly happy.

477
00:31:40.285 --> 00:31:42.203
-Who is it?
-MRS. POTTS: Mrs. Potts, dear.


478
00:31:44.414 --> 00:31:45.582
-I thought you might like...

479
00:31:45.665 --> 00:31:47.333
-A spot of tea.
-But you're...


480
00:31:47.584 --> 00:31:50.128
-you're a...
-Oh!


481
00:31:50.253 --> 00:31:52.338
-Careful.
-This is impossible.


482
00:31:52.672 --> 00:31:55.300
I know it is, but here we are.

483
00:31:55.508 --> 00:31:57.886
That was a very brave thing
you did, my dear.


484
00:31:58.094 --> 00:31:59.429
We all think so.

485
00:31:59.554 --> 00:32:03.099
But I've lost my father,
my dreams, everything.


486
00:32:03.266 --> 00:32:04.893
Cheer up, child.

487
00:32:05.435 --> 00:32:08.980
It'll turn out all right in the end.
You'll see.


488
00:32:09.355 --> 00:32:11.190
Oh, listen to me, jabbering on

489
00:32:11.274 --> 00:32:13.192
while there's a supper
to get on the table.


490
00:32:13.359 --> 00:32:14.277
Chip!

491
00:32:15.403 --> 00:32:16.487
Bye!

492
00:32:16.696 --> 00:32:19.490
What's taking so long?

493
00:32:20.033 --> 00:32:23.411
I told her to come down.
Why isn't she here yet?


494
00:32:23.661 --> 00:32:25.246
Oh, try to be patient, sir.

495
00:32:25.496 --> 00:32:28.833
The girl has lost her father
and her freedom all in one day.


496
00:32:29.125 --> 00:32:31.878
Master, have you thought
that perhaps this girl


497
00:32:31.961 --> 00:32:34.631
-could be the one to break the spell?
-Of course I have!


498
00:32:35.006 --> 00:32:36.925
-I'm not a fool.
-Good.


499
00:32:37.216 --> 00:32:40.762
So you fall in love with her,
she falls in love with you,


500
00:32:40.845 --> 00:32:42.722
and poof, the spell is broken.

501
00:32:42.805 --> 00:32:44.724
We'll be human again
by midnight.


502
00:32:44.807 --> 00:32:47.727
Oh, it's not that easy, Lumière.
These things take time.


503
00:32:47.810 --> 00:32:49.938
But the rose has already
begun to wilt.


504
00:32:50.021 --> 00:32:51.648
Oh, it's no use.

505
00:32:52.440 --> 00:32:54.108
She's so beautiful, and I'm...

506
00:32:54.859 --> 00:32:55.944
well, look at me!

507
00:32:58.363 --> 00:33:01.074
Oh, you must help her
to see past all that.


508
00:33:01.407 --> 00:33:02.492
I don't know how.

509
00:33:03.534 --> 00:33:06.037
Well, you can start by making yourself
more presentable.


510
00:33:06.287 --> 00:33:08.331
Straighten up.
Try to act like a gentleman.


511
00:33:08.414 --> 00:33:12.126
Ah, yes. When she comes in,
give her a dashing, debonair smile.


512
00:33:12.585 --> 00:33:13.962
Come, come. Show me the smile.

513
00:33:14.712 --> 00:33:19.092
-But don't frighten the poor girl.
-Impress her with your rapier wit.


514
00:33:19.175 --> 00:33:20.259
But be gentle.

515
00:33:20.677 --> 00:33:22.762
-Shower her with compliments.
-MRS. POTTS: But be sincere.


516
00:33:22.845 --> 00:33:24.138
And above all...

517
00:33:24.305 --> 00:33:26.349
You must control your temper.

518
00:33:26.641 --> 00:33:28.559
-Here she is.

519
00:33:30.687 --> 00:33:31.980
Good evening.

520
00:33:33.272 --> 00:33:34.774
Well? Where is she?

521
00:33:35.942 --> 00:33:36.901
What?

522
00:33:37.610 --> 00:33:40.363
<i>But Your Grace, 
Your Eminence...</i>

523
00:33:41.072 --> 00:33:42.657
<i>let's not be hasty!</i>

524
00:33:45.493 --> 00:33:47.245
I thought I told you
to come down to dinner.


525
00:33:47.412 --> 00:33:48.538
I'm not hungry.

526
00:33:49.539 --> 00:33:52.667
You'll come out, or I'll...
I'll... I'll break down the door!


527
00:33:53.042 --> 00:33:55.545
Master, I could be wrong,
but, uh...


528
00:33:55.628 --> 00:33:59.132
That may not be the best way
to win the girl's affections.


529
00:33:59.298 --> 00:34:02.677
Please, attempt to be a gentleman.

530
00:34:02.885 --> 00:34:06.055
It would give me
great pleasure


531
00:34:07.098 --> 00:34:08.891
if you would join me
for dinner.


532
00:34:08.975 --> 00:34:10.018
We say please.

533
00:34:11.060 --> 00:34:12.478
-Please.
-No, thank you.


534
00:34:12.645 --> 00:34:14.188
You can't stay in there forever.

535
00:34:14.272 --> 00:34:16.190
-Yes, I can.
-Fine!


536
00:34:16.274 --> 00:34:19.569
Then go ahead and starve!

537
00:34:19.736 --> 00:34:21.571
If she doesn't eat with me,

538
00:34:22.113 --> 00:34:23.906
then she doesn't eat at all.

539
00:34:27.201 --> 00:34:28.536
-Oh, dear.

540
00:34:28.661 --> 00:34:30.246
That didn't go very well
at all, did it?


541
00:34:32.457 --> 00:34:35.084
What does she want me to do? Beg?

542
00:34:41.507 --> 00:34:42.800
Show me the girl.

543
00:34:43.551 --> 00:34:46.763
<i>But the master's really not so bad</i>
<i>once you get to know him.</i>


544
00:34:47.180 --> 00:34:49.057
<i>Why don't you give him</i>
<i>a chance?</i>


545
00:34:49.265 --> 00:34:50.892
<i>I don't want to get to know him.</i>

546
00:34:51.100 --> 00:34:53.227
<i>I don't want to have</i>
<i>anything to do with him.</i>


547
00:34:55.938 --> 00:34:57.857
I'm just fooling myself.

548
00:34:58.733 --> 00:35:02.111
She'll never see me as anything
but a monster.


549
00:35:06.908 --> 00:35:07.909
It's hopeless.

550
00:36:37.498 --> 00:36:40.626
The falling petals
of an enchanted rose,


551
00:36:41.210 --> 00:36:43.296
each one a graceful reminder

552
00:36:43.421 --> 00:36:47.258
that love is as fragile
as it is enduring,


553
00:36:47.675 --> 00:36:52.430
as difficult to find
as it is a wonder to hold onto.


554
00:36:52.972 --> 00:36:56.017
That true love can overcome
any obstacles


555
00:36:56.100 --> 00:36:59.270
no matter how impossible
they may seem.


556
00:36:59.979 --> 00:37:03.566
<i>It is this idea that inspired</i>
<i>Walt Disney himself</i>


557
00:37:03.649 --> 00:37:06.736
<i>to want to tell the story</i>
<i>of</i>Beauty and the Beast


558
00:37:06.819 --> 00:37:09.113
<i>as far back as the 1930s.</i>

559
00:37:10.156 --> 00:37:14.994
<i>For decades, Disney artists worked</i>
<i>to adapt this tale as old as time,</i>


560
00:37:15.119 --> 00:37:18.497
<i>yet something was always missing</i>
<i>from these early efforts.</i>


561
00:37:18.915 --> 00:37:23.127
<i>Then, more than 50 years</i>
<i>after inspiration first struck,</i>


562
00:37:23.211 --> 00:37:28.466
<i>a team came together that was just</i>
<i>as special as the fairy tale itself.</i>


563
00:37:28.716 --> 00:37:30.801
<i>Dancing again, we'll be twirling again</i>

564
00:37:30.885 --> 00:37:31.844
-Yeah.
-Want that faster?


565
00:37:31.928 --> 00:37:34.222
-Yeah.
<i>-Composer Alan Menken,</i>


566
00:37:34.388 --> 00:37:35.890
<i>lyricist Howard Ashman,</i>

567
00:37:35.973 --> 00:37:38.351
<i>and the team at Walt Disney</i>
<i>Animation Studios</i>


568
00:37:38.434 --> 00:37:41.187
<i>found the missing spark.</i>

569
00:37:41.479 --> 00:37:46.275
<i>Together with Linda Woolverton,</i>
<i>the first woman ever to write</i>


570
00:37:46.359 --> 00:37:49.987
<i>an animated feature for Disney,</i>
<i>they brought the story to life</i>


571
00:37:50.071 --> 00:37:53.407
<i>not simply through words,</i>
<i>but through music,</i>


572
00:37:53.574 --> 00:37:57.495
<i>and were finally able to deliver</i>
<i>on Walt Disney's dream.</i>


573
00:37:57.787 --> 00:38:00.706
<i>Roy Disney himself wrote</i>
<i>the film's prologue.</i>


574
00:38:00.790 --> 00:38:03.459
<i>Together, they embraced</i>
<i>all the joy</i>


575
00:38:03.542 --> 00:38:06.379
<i>of Belle becoming the hero</i>
<i>of her own story...</i>


576
00:38:06.504 --> 00:38:09.215
I want excitement
and adventure in my life.


577
00:38:09.882 --> 00:38:12.009
And I want someone
to share it with.


578
00:38:12.176 --> 00:38:16.013
<i>And the magic of the Beast</i>
<i>and his enchanted castle.</i>


579
00:38:16.555 --> 00:38:18.349
Beauty and the Beast <i>has become</i>

580
00:38:18.432 --> 00:38:23.020
one of the most beloved
animated classics ever made.


581
00:38:23.562 --> 00:38:27.733
It was even
the first animated film ever


582
00:38:27.817 --> 00:38:31.445
to be nominated for Best Picture
at the Academy Awards.


583
00:38:32.530 --> 00:38:33.781
And to this day,

584
00:38:34.615 --> 00:38:39.203
Walt Disney's original idea
continues to inspire us all.


585
00:38:48.921 --> 00:38:52.174
<i>Come on, Chip, into the cupboard</i>
<i>with your brothers and sisters.</i>


586
00:38:54.010 --> 00:38:56.929
-But I'm not sleepy.
-Yes, you are.


587
00:38:57.054 --> 00:38:58.806
-No, I'm not.

588
00:38:58.889 --> 00:39:01.934
Well, if you ask me,
she was just being stubborn.


589
00:39:02.018 --> 00:39:03.602
After all, he did say "please."

590
00:39:03.686 --> 00:39:06.480
But if the master doesn't learn
to control that temper,


591
00:39:06.564 --> 00:39:08.899
-He'll never break...
-Splendid to see you


592
00:39:08.983 --> 00:39:10.192
out and about, mademoiselle.

593
00:39:10.735 --> 00:39:13.112
I am Cogsworth,
head of the household.


594
00:39:13.195 --> 00:39:15.031
-Ah.

595
00:39:15.573 --> 00:39:18.451
-This is Lumière.
<i>-Enchanté, chérie.</i>


596
00:39:18.784 --> 00:39:22.496
If there's... stop that...
anything we... please... can do


597
00:39:22.580 --> 00:39:24.165
to make your stay
more comfortable...


598
00:39:24.248 --> 00:39:25.249
-Ow!

599
00:39:25.374 --> 00:39:27.543
-I am a little hungry.
-You are?


600
00:39:27.752 --> 00:39:29.337
Hear that? She's hungry.

601
00:39:29.712 --> 00:39:32.465
Stoke the fire. Break out the silver.
Wake the china.


602
00:39:32.798 --> 00:39:35.051
Remember what the master said?

603
00:39:35.217 --> 00:39:38.387
Oh, pish-posh. I'm not about to let
the poor child go hungry.


604
00:39:38.554 --> 00:39:39.847
All right, fine.

605
00:39:39.930 --> 00:39:41.474
Glass of water, crust of bread,
and then...


606
00:39:41.599 --> 00:39:43.934
Cogsworth, I am surprised at you.

607
00:39:44.226 --> 00:39:46.604
She's not a prisoner.
She's our guest.


608
00:39:46.771 --> 00:39:48.731
We must make her feel
welcome here.


609
00:39:48.939 --> 00:39:52.109
-Right this way, mademoiselle.
-Well, keep it down.


610
00:39:52.526 --> 00:39:54.904
If the master finds out about this,
it will be our necks.


611
00:39:54.987 --> 00:39:56.530
Of course, of course.

612
00:39:56.864 --> 00:39:59.742
But what is dinner
without a little music?


613
00:40:00.117 --> 00:40:01.452
-Music?

614
00:40:03.829 --> 00:40:05.790
<i>Ma cheré mademoiselle,</i>

615
00:40:05.873 --> 00:40:08.834
it is with deepest pride
and greatest pleasure


616
00:40:09.001 --> 00:40:11.837
that we welcome you
here tonight.


617
00:40:12.254 --> 00:40:16.092
And now we invite you
to relax and to pull up a chair


618
00:40:16.175 --> 00:40:21.389
as the dining room
proudly presents your dinner.


619
00:40:22.807 --> 00:40:26.685
<i>Be our guest</i>

620
00:40:26.769 --> 00:40:30.106
<i>Be our guest</i>
<i>Put our service to the test</i>


621
00:40:30.314 --> 00:40:34.527
<i>Tie a napkin 'round your neck, chérie</i>
<i>And we'll provide the rest</i>


622
00:40:34.985 --> 00:40:37.488
<i>Soup du jour, hot hors d'oeuvres</i>

623
00:40:37.571 --> 00:40:39.532
<i>Why, we only live to serve</i>

624
00:40:39.615 --> 00:40:41.784
<i>Try the gray stuff, it's delicious</i>

625
00:40:41.867 --> 00:40:43.702
<i>Don't believe me</i>
<i>Ask the dishes</i>


626
00:40:43.869 --> 00:40:48.791
<i>They can sing, they can dance</i>
<i>After all, miss, this is France</i>


627
00:40:48.874 --> 00:40:52.795
<i>And a dinner here is never second best</i>

628
00:40:52.878 --> 00:40:55.131
<i>Go on, unfold your menu</i>

629
00:40:55.214 --> 00:40:58.300
<i>Take a glance</i>
<i>And then you'll be our guest</i>


630
00:40:58.592 --> 00:41:01.387
Oui,<i>our guest, be our guest</i>

631
00:41:01.762 --> 00:41:06.183
<i>Beef ragout, cheese soufflé</i>
<i>Pie and pudding en flambé</i>


632
00:41:06.267 --> 00:41:10.479
<i>We'll prepare and serve with flair</i>
<i>A culinary cabaret</i>


633
00:41:10.563 --> 00:41:14.859
<i>You're alone and you're scared</i>
<i>But the banquet's all prepared</i>


634
00:41:14.942 --> 00:41:19.405
<i>No one's gloomy or complaining</i>
<i>While the flatware is entertaining</i>


635
00:41:19.697 --> 00:41:23.409
<i>We tell jokes, I do tricks</i>
<i>With my fellow candlesticks</i>


636
00:41:23.492 --> 00:41:27.288
<i>And it's all in perfect taste</i>
<i>That you can bet</i>


637
00:41:27.371 --> 00:41:29.373
<i>Come on and lift your glass</i>

638
00:41:29.457 --> 00:41:31.625
<i>You've won your own free pass</i>

639
00:41:31.709 --> 00:41:33.127
<i>To be our guest</i>

640
00:41:33.210 --> 00:41:35.963
<i>If you're stressed</i>
<i>It's fine dining we suggest</i>


641
00:41:36.088 --> 00:41:39.842
<i>Be our guest</i>
<i>Be our guest, be our guest</i>


642
00:41:41.427 --> 00:41:43.846
<i>Life is so unnerving</i>

643
00:41:44.054 --> 00:41:46.390
<i>For a servant who's not serving</i>

644
00:41:46.515 --> 00:41:50.060
<i>He's not whole without
a soul to wait upon</i>

645
00:41:51.312 --> 00:41:55.608
<i>Oh, those good old days</i>
<i>When we were useful</i>


646
00:41:56.400 --> 00:41:59.487
<i>Suddenly those good old days are gone</i>

647
00:42:01.071 --> 00:42:05.326
<i>Ten years we've been rusting</i>
<i>Needing so much more than dusting</i>


648
00:42:05.659 --> 00:42:09.538
<i>Needing exercise</i>
<i>A chance to use our skills</i>


649
00:42:11.081 --> 00:42:15.419
<i>Most days we just lay</i>
<i>Around the castle</i>


650
00:42:15.794 --> 00:42:19.798
<i>Flabby, fat, and lazy</i>
<i>You walked in and oopsie-daisy</i>


651
00:42:20.758 --> 00:42:22.593
<i>Ma cheré mademoiselle,</i>

652
00:42:22.676 --> 00:42:26.138
it is my honor to present
my favorite cup of tea,


653
00:42:26.388 --> 00:42:28.933
the incomparable Mrs. Potts.

654
00:42:29.266 --> 00:42:31.185
<i>It's a guest, it's a guest</i>

655
00:42:31.352 --> 00:42:32.770
<i>Sakes alive and I'll be blessed</i>

656
00:42:33.187 --> 00:42:34.897
<i>Wine's been poured</i>
<i>And thank the Lord</i>


657
00:42:35.064 --> 00:42:36.899
<i>I've had the napkins freshly pressed</i>

658
00:42:37.066 --> 00:42:40.486
<i>With dessert, she'll want tea</i>
<i>And my dear, that's fine with me</i>


659
00:42:40.778 --> 00:42:44.740
<i>While the cups do their soft-shoein'</i>
<i>I'll be bubblin', I'll be brewin'</i>


660
00:42:44.823 --> 00:42:48.494
<i>I'll get warm, piping hot</i>
<i>Heaven's sakes, is that a spot</i>


661
00:42:48.661 --> 00:42:51.997
<i>Clean it up,</i>
<i>We want the company impressed</i>


662
00:42:52.164 --> 00:42:56.001
<i>We've got a lot to do</i>
<i>Is it one lump or two</i>


663
00:42:56.168 --> 00:42:57.670
<i>For you, our guest</i>

664
00:42:57.753 --> 00:42:59.463
<i>-She's our guest</i>
<i>-Oh, she's our guest</i>


665
00:42:59.547 --> 00:43:02.007
-<i>Be our guest</i>
<i>-Be our guest, be our guest</i>


666
00:43:02.132 --> 00:43:03.759
<i>Our command is your request</i>

667
